\f0\fs64 \cf2 Lemon Pound Cake I\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\sa360\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs38 \cf3 Servings: 8 to 10\uc0\u8232 
\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\sa360\ql\qnatural

\b\fs50 \cf3 INGREDIENTS
\b0 \uc0\u8232 3 cups flour\u8232 \'bd teaspoon baking powder\u8232 \'bd teaspoon baking soda\u8232 \'bd teaspoon salt\u8232 1 cup (2 sticks) unsalted butter, softened\u8232 2 cups sugar \u8232 4 eggs\u8232 \'be cup buttermilk\u8232 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\u8232 \'bd teaspoon almond extract \u8232 Zest and juice of one large lemon, divided\

\b Tip:
\b0  Lemon zest adds brightness to the flavor of baked goods. When removing it from the fruit, try using a microplane grater, available at your local grocery store. The microplane only lifts the bright yellow zest, and not the white pith beneath, which can infuse your batter with a dull, bitter taste.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\ql\qnatural

\b \cf3 INSTRUCTIONS
\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl360\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf3 {\listtext	1.	}Preheat oven to 325\'b0F. Grease a 12\'94 cake or bunt pan, then lightly coat with flour, tapping out excess.\
{\listtext	2.	}In a medium-size bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt, then set aside.\
{\listtext	3.	}In a large bowl, combine butter and sugar, beating with an electric mixer at medium speed for one minute, or until light and creamy. Add eggs one at a time to the mixture, beating well after each addition.\
{\listtext	4.	}Gradually add in portions of the dry mixture and buttermilk until the batter is well mixed. Stir in vanilla extract, almond extract, finely chopped lemon zest and 3 tablespoons lemon juice; mix just until combined.\
{\listtext	5.	}Spread the batter evenly into your prepared cake pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the cake\'92s center comes out clean.\
{\listtext	6.	}Let cool for 10 minutes, then remove from the pan. Brush the warm cake liberally with Lemon Syrup (see instructions below).\
{\listtext	7.	}Once coated, let cool completely on a wire rack. Drizzle your cake with\
		Lemon Glaze. (recipe below)\
