\f0\fs64 \cf2 \ulnone Lemon Syrup and Glaze\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\sa360\ql\qnatural

\f1\b\fs50 \cf3 INGREDIENTS
\b0 \uc0\u8232 \'bd cup granulated sugar\u8232 \'bd cup water\u8232 Juice and peel of one large lemon (plus reserved juice and zest from cake batter)\u8232 1 cup powdered sugar\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\ql\qnatural

\b \cf3 INSTRUCTIONS
\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl360\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0\cf3 {\listtext	1.	}To create your Lemon Syrup, combine sugar, water, lemon juice and peel in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil.\
{\listtext	2.	}Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove and discard lemon peel.\
{\listtext	3.	}When your syrup is ready, place the cake and cooling rack on a rimmed baking sheet to simplify cleanup. With a large culinary brush, generously coat your warm cake with the syrup, letting it drip over the sides of the cake. Set aside 3 tablespoons syrup to prepare the Lemon Glaze.\
{\listtext	4.	}To make your glaze, combine 1 cup powdered sugar and remaining lemon syrup in a medium-size bowl, then drizzle it over the cooled cake.\
